reviewText: This album along with all other Marty Robbins albums are exceptional. There never was neither has been a writer/singer such as Marty. I had the priveledge of meeting him and he was a very down to earth, humble person grateful for all that people did for him. Marty's music seemed to come from the heart. His grandfather was an Arizona Ranger and it is evident he developed a love and romance of this era gone bye.
